column5: It's cold and windy out but the worms are out. I was done in 10 minutes. Get out there now if you pick yours.
wanna go out for another ten minutes and ill buy em off ya ...lol...worms are hard to find up here... how much for a coolwhip container...(not even joking)
just finished aswell, just under 200 id say within a couple of smokes!
time measured in smokes....distance measured in beers...its great to be a canadian!
yeah well too bad i won't go fishing until next week
Put a little dirt in the container and then put the worms in the fridge. They will keep for months in the fridge....
Get Harper, Ignatief & Leyton to do a debate over your worm container . . . .    the bull generated in only a few minutes should keep those worms fed forever!
As soon as you adopt the 5 gallon bucket for volume then you will be a proud member of the  new redneck Canadian units of measurement revolution.   Art
